1
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:11,600
<i>I can see
she has great potential.</i>

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:13,400
<i> She's not just pretty.</i>

3
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:15,733
<i>She's talented, smart, and kind.</i>

4
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:17,233
<i>Yeah. And she trusts people
way too much.</i>

5
00:00:17,367 --> 00:00:19,400
<i>That's why others
take advantage of her.</i>

6
00:00:19,533 --> 00:00:20,767
<i>- Like who?
- Can we talk</i>

7
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:23,133
<i>about something else?
Not about Marj. Please.</i>

8
00:00:23,267 --> 00:00:25,467
<i> She chose Dad! Let her go.</i>

9
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:29,667
<i> Mom!</i>

10
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:32,433
<i>Thanks again for helping
with Jobert earlier.</i>

11
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:34,300
<i> I know you're Miss Tough Girl,</i>

12
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:36,900
<i> but you get tired, too, right?</i>

13
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:38,567
<i> Marj, don't let him fool you.</i>

14
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:39,567
<i> He's not a good guy.</i>

15
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,133
<i>Marj, you and I belong together.</i>

16
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,933
<i> I hope you choose me.</i>

17
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:49,133
Edward, you were the first
person I really clicked with

18
00:00:49,267 --> 00:00:50,567
at the office.

19
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:52,033
Back when I was new.

20
00:00:53,267 --> 00:00:54,767
But...

21
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:58,100
You don't have
to answer me now.

22
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:00,400
But, Edward...

23
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:02,333
I don't want to pressure you
to decide today.

24
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:07,133
I just needed you to know...

25
00:01:08,367 --> 00:01:11,667
how I really feel about you.

26
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:14,900
I hope you think
about everything I said.

27
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,233
Marj...

28
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:24,833
I only want
what's best for you.

29
00:01:25,933 --> 00:01:27,733
And Paolo isn't it.

30
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:35,467
Thanks for hearing me out.

31
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:39,733
See you at work.

32
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:47,033
<i> He admitted to me</i>

33
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,467
<i>that something happened
between you two in Batangas.</i>

34
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,567
<i> Honestly, I felt betrayed.</i>

35
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:53,833
<i>Because Paolo knew I liked you.</i>

36
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:07,900
<i>Thanks again for helping
with Jobert earlier,</i>

37
00:03:08,033 --> 00:03:09,767
<i> even if it was just for a bit.</i>

38
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:15,467
<i>Sometimes you have to admit
to yourself that you need help.</i>

39
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:19,133
<i>So this is what it feels like
to not carry everything alone.</i>

40
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:22,733
<i>That's what he wants you
to feel.</i>

41
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:25,967
<i>He'll do anything
to make you like him.</i>

42
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:29,600
<i>Then, in the end,
he'll leave you.</i>

43
00:03:29,733 --> 00:03:31,033
<i> He'll drop you.</i>

44
00:03:31,167 --> 00:03:32,833
<i>And you're the one
who gets hurt.</i>

45
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:34,800
<i> That's the kind of man he is.</i>

46
00:03:40,733 --> 00:03:43,233
Sis, your phone's ringing.

47
00:03:43,367 --> 00:03:45,567
Someone's calling.

48
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,633
It's Paolo.

49
00:03:50,767 --> 00:03:52,433
Why don't you answer?

50
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:54,767
It's Kind Big Bro.

51
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:56,300
It's late.

52
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:02,500
Marj.

53
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:08,133
When is Kind Big Bro
coming here again?

54
00:04:11,667 --> 00:04:13,900
I like him.

55
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:18,500
I hope he's always with us.

56
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,233
I want him for you, Sis.

57
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:25,567
Because he loves you.

58
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:41,000
Come on.

59
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:42,133
Hi, Sir. Good morning.

60
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:43,700
Good morning.

61
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,867
So...

62
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,300
how was your talk with Edward?

63
00:04:57,067 --> 00:04:58,833
It was okay.

64
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:02,800
Do you want to talk about it?

65
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:11,900
I don't think

66
00:05:12,033 --> 00:05:14,767
this is an appropriate place
to talk about it, Sir.

67
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:18,567
Sir?

68
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:20,533
There you go again with "sir."

69
00:05:23,633 --> 00:05:26,100
Sorry.

70
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:28,933
I just have a lot
to take care of, Sir.

71
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:31,900
Excuse me.

72
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:33,467
Your copies.

73
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:10,067
What did you say to Marj?

74
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,333
- What?
- Why?

75
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:12,333
What could I have told her?

76
00:06:12,467 --> 00:06:13,667
I don't know.

77
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,800
She's suddenly avoiding me.

78
00:06:14,933 --> 00:06:16,767
She's not replying
to my messages!

79
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:19,867
- What did you tell her?
- What did I tell her?

80
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,100
The truth.

81
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:23,400
That she's just a conquest
to you.

82
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:26,067
Your flavor of the month.

83
00:06:32,567 --> 00:06:35,367
What did you say to Marj?

84
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:38,167
- Hey!
- What did you say to Marj?

85
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:40,300
- What is this? Stop!
- Explain!

86
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:41,733
What's going on?

87
00:06:43,233 --> 00:06:45,267
You know what?

88
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,167
I know what this is about.

89
00:06:48,567 --> 00:06:50,467
It's that woman, right?

90
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,433
Marj, isn't it?

91
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,233
Miss Castillo?

92
00:06:59,267 --> 00:07:01,067
You're fighting over one woman

93
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:05,100
when you have a million
to choose from?

94
00:07:06,133 --> 00:07:08,300
This is ridiculous.

95
00:07:08,433 --> 00:07:09,733
Get it together.

96
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:12,100
You're embarrassing
the Torrecampo name.

97
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:17,600
What?

98
00:07:48,433 --> 00:07:49,767
Looking for a place to rent?

99
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:54,333
- Yeah.
- You're moving?

100
00:07:54,467 --> 00:07:57,833
Just looking for somewhere close
to the office

101
00:07:57,967 --> 00:08:01,000
so I can be with Jobert
during lunch.

102
00:08:02,433 --> 00:08:04,167
I can help you with that.

103
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:06,333
No, it's okay.

104
00:08:06,467 --> 00:08:07,433
Thanks.

105
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:11,333
Are you avoiding me?

106
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:13,133
Do I disgust you?

107
00:08:13,267 --> 00:08:14,900
No. It's not like that.

108
00:08:15,033 --> 00:08:16,467
Then why won't you look at me?

109
00:08:19,567 --> 00:08:22,600
Is this because of what Edward
said about me?

110
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:24,100
Because they're not true.

111
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:29,500
So you don't have
a flavor of the month?

112
00:08:29,633 --> 00:08:30,967
Well...

113
00:08:34,367 --> 00:08:38,000
Why did I even ask?
That's none of my business.

114
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:41,633
You want the truth?

115
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:43,967
Fine.

116
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,500
Let's talk about it.

117
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,400
Ask away.

118
00:08:48,533 --> 00:08:50,500
Ask me anything.

119
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:52,400
Even the most
uncomfortable ones.

120
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,700
I will answer.

121
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,333
I won't lie.

122
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:03,267
You want to know
how many women I've slept with?

123
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,833
Honestly? I don't know.

124
00:09:07,967 --> 00:09:09,967
I don't count.

125
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,467
But one thing's for sure.

126
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:14,000
What happened between us?

127
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,233
That was the most memorable.

128
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:20,000
And I'm not lying.

129
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:23,833
I'm not sweet-talking you just
to get you back in bed.

130
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:30,900
That's not why I'm pulling away.

131
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:37,267
And it's not just because
you're a womanizer.

132
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:38,833
Or the kind of man you are.

133
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:42,367
Then what?

134
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:45,033
I don't want you two fighting
because of me.

135
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,133
I don't want this
to happen again.

136
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:53,667
So to keep the peace,

137
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,267
I'll be the one who stays away
from both of you.

138
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:08,867
So, girl, did you like that
apartment we checked out?

139
00:10:10,133 --> 00:10:12,500
Yeah, but the rent's
way out of my budget.

140
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:13,933
It's pretty expensive.

141
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:17,300
Well, I can't really blame them.
This area's pricey.

142
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:20,767
I just liked it because
it's close to the office,

143
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,233
in case of emergencies.

144
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:24,767
Think about it first.

145
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:27,133
Because once Jobert
starts school,

146
00:10:27,267 --> 00:10:29,900
it won't even be close
anymore anyway.

147
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:43,867
Aren't you going to answer that?

148
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,500
What if it's work?

149
00:10:45,633 --> 00:10:47,800
Not everything's about
your love triangle.

150
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,033
Hey, hottie.

151
00:11:36,167 --> 00:11:37,233
This one's on me.

152
00:11:39,867 --> 00:11:41,567
No, I'm good.
Thanks, though.

153
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:43,200
You sure?

154
00:11:50,933 --> 00:11:52,267
What's your name?

155
00:11:53,733 --> 00:11:54,733
Sorry.

156
00:11:56,167 --> 00:11:58,500
Sorry? That's your name?

157
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:00,900
No,

158
00:12:01,033 --> 00:12:02,733
Sorry, I'm into someone else.

159
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:05,200
So? She doesn't have to know.

160
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,233
Still. I don't want
to disappoint her.

161
00:12:09,367 --> 00:12:11,033
I'm sorry.

162
00:12:24,633 --> 00:12:26,400
All right, people,
we need to step it up!

163
00:12:26,533 --> 00:12:27,867
We're slowing down.

164
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,167
Push who needs pushing.
Follow up harder.

165
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:32,733
The company's not the only one
that benefits from this.

166
00:12:32,867 --> 00:12:34,700
You do, too.

167
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,200
Got it?

168
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:37,700
Meeting adjourned.

169
00:12:39,233 --> 00:12:40,700
Ms. Castillo.

170
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:53,367
Someone wants to view our New
Manila listing this afternoon.

171
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,567
Make sure you're on time.

172
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:57,067
The client will meet you there.

173
00:12:59,067 --> 00:13:00,967
Yes, Sir.
I'll take care of it.

174
00:13:13,367 --> 00:13:14,967
Sir Paolo, I'm here already,

175
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:17,133
but the client
hasn't arrived yet.

176
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:19,067
Maybe they went ahead
to the property?

177
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,667
All right, I'm here, too.

178
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:27,733
Sir Paolo?

179
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:32,533
You know, I still prefer
not being called "sir."

180
00:13:34,767 --> 00:13:36,533
What are you doing here?

181
00:13:36,667 --> 00:13:38,867
Oh, are you meeting
the client, too?

182
00:13:40,267 --> 00:13:42,000
There is no client.

183
00:13:43,033 --> 00:13:44,333
What?

184
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:48,500
This was the only way
I could think of to talk to you.

185
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:54,000
Didn't we already
talk about this?

186
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:58,067
It's better if I just stay
away from both of you.

187
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,867
That's the fair thing to do.

188
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,333
You need to give me
a fair chance, too.

189
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:05,900
If my brother were able
to confess to you,

190
00:14:06,033 --> 00:14:07,800
then I should also be allowed
to confess.

191
00:14:10,167 --> 00:14:11,500
Marj...

192
00:14:11,633 --> 00:14:13,000
I really like you.

193
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:18,233
Ever since Batangas,

194
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:21,067
I can't stop thinking about you.

195
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,433
How many girls
have you used that line on?

196
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,067
You don't believe me?

197
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,633
I don't blame you.

198
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:36,267
But I want you to know
I'm serious about how I feel.

199
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:43,700
Yeah, I admit, I'm not really
the courting type.

200
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:45,667
But if that's what it takes...

201
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:50,400
to prove that I like you,

202
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:52,367
I'm serious about you,

203
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:55,667
then I'll do it.

204
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:57,133
Marj...

205
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:08,500
I really like you, Marj.

206
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,300
And I want you
to be my girlfriend.

207
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,600
Your love life is wild, girl!

208
00:15:28,733 --> 00:15:31,867
Hey! This is a serious problem.

209
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,867
How is that a serious problem?

210
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,767
The Torrecampo brothers

211
00:15:35,933 --> 00:15:38,933
just confessed their feelings
to you.

212
00:15:39,067 --> 00:15:40,867
And you haven't answered
either of them yet.

213
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,600
You just have to pick one.

214
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:44,367
You win either way.

215
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,300
It's not that simple.

216
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:49,033
You like them both, yes.

217
00:15:49,167 --> 00:15:51,433
So? Which one
do you actually like?

218
00:15:54,433 --> 00:15:57,100
That's the thing.
I can't choose.

219
00:15:57,233 --> 00:16:00,500
Either way,
it just causes trouble.

220
00:16:00,633 --> 00:16:03,267
They're already fighting
because of it.

221
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:06,300
But think about it, girl.

222
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:10,967
Whoever you choose,
it'll solve your problem.

223
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:13,200
Someone will finally
be there for you.

224
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:14,967
You won't have to go
through everything alone.

225
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,333
Of all people,

226
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:46,267
it had to be your own brother

227
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:49,400
who ended up competing with you
over Marj.

228
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,133
Dad, please.
Spare me tonight.

229
00:16:53,267 --> 00:16:54,933
Please don't lecture me
right now.

230
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:56,700
Hey,

231
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,900
I'm not saying anything.

232
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:01,233
But let me tell you this.

233
00:17:01,367 --> 00:17:04,400
I didn't raise you
to be a loser.

234
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:06,400
What?

235
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:08,833
Do you mean...

236
00:17:08,967 --> 00:17:11,833
Don't lose to your brother.

237
00:17:11,967 --> 00:17:13,300
There, I said it.

238
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:19,667
Normally, fathers would say,

239
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,833
"Don't fight with your brother."

240
00:17:21,967 --> 00:17:24,967
So why are you telling me this?

241
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:26,067
Because...

242
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:30,133
if there's anyone...

243
00:17:30,267 --> 00:17:32,667
I want you to end up marrying,

244
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,133
it's someone like Marj.

245
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:38,533
I'm retiring soon.

246
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:43,267
And I want to be sure
the company's in good hands.

247
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,133
She'd be good for you.

248
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:49,633
She can be an asset to this
family and to the company.

249
00:17:52,033 --> 00:17:57,100
Would it be the same
if she ended up with Edward?

250
00:17:57,233 --> 00:17:58,233
Wouldn't it?

251
00:17:59,267 --> 00:18:02,267
I'd rather my golden child
win the trophy.

252
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:06,200
Dad, please don't call Marj
a trophy.

253
00:18:07,233 --> 00:18:08,900
She's a person.

254
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:11,900
And please go easy on Edward.

255
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:14,133
Because...

256
00:18:14,267 --> 00:18:16,400
it just makes him
resent me more.

257
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:19,200
He feels like
you always favor me.

258
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:23,267
Everything I do,

259
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:25,500
every decision I make,

260
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:29,567
is for the best interest
of this family and our company.

261
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:32,867
That's why I want
you and Marj together.

262
00:18:34,033 --> 00:18:37,467
You're the future
of Torrecampo Realty.

263
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:44,667
So if I were you,
I wouldn't let Marj slip away.

264
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,500
You might never find someone
like her again.

265
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:52,267
Think.

266
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,667
So...

267
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,433
what do you think?

268
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:34,633
Am I doing this right?

269
00:19:38,467 --> 00:19:40,200
I don't know.

270
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:43,800
I've never received
this many roses before.

271
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:50,433
You've been asked
out before, right?

272
00:19:50,567 --> 00:19:52,467
Can I take you to lunch?

273
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,967
So this is how hard it is
to wait for an answer, huh?

274
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,333
It's okay if you say no.

275
00:20:11,467 --> 00:20:14,967
I can just ask again tomorrow.

276
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:16,800
Or the day after.

277
00:20:16,933 --> 00:20:18,400
Or the next day.

278
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:23,667
I'll keep asking
until you change your mind.

279
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,267
Until you say yes.

280
00:20:31,133 --> 00:20:32,233
Jobert!

281
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:34,267
Hey, hey, calm down.

282
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,967
Easy, Jobert.

283
00:20:36,133 --> 00:20:36,867
We're getting Pong.

284
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,067
We're getting Pong, Jobert!

285
00:20:40,933 --> 00:20:42,733
Hello, Hannah?

286
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:43,933
Marj!

287
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:46,300
I was supposed to leave earlier,
but Jobert's losing it,

288
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:47,433
you know how he is.
I can't calm him down.

289
00:20:47,567 --> 00:20:49,500
He's throwing a tantrum,
looking for Aunt Evelyn!

290
00:20:49,633 --> 00:20:51,867
Okay, don't leave yet.
Stay there with Jobert.

291
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,300
I'm coming home.

292
00:20:53,433 --> 00:20:54,667
Did something happen to Jobert?

293
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:56,500
I need to go home.

294
00:20:56,633 --> 00:20:57,733
Come on, I'll take you.

295
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:58,833
Let's go.

296
00:21:21,967 --> 00:21:23,067
Jobert!

297
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,433
Jobert, I'm here.

298
00:21:25,567 --> 00:21:28,767
Where's Mom? I want Mom!

299
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:31,967
Jobert, remember, I already
explained this to you.

300
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:34,533
Mom's staying with Dad for now.

301
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:36,533
And when she's not busy anymore,

302
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:39,200
she'll come back and visit you.

303
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:40,267
Jobert.

304
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:42,067
Why did you
make Mom leave?

305
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:44,333
- Why did you make Mom leave?
- Jobert, Jobert. Easy, easy.

306
00:21:44,467 --> 00:21:46,867
Jobert!

307
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,667
Mom wanted to leave!
I didn't decide that!

308
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:52,300
- It was Mom's choice!
- It's your fault!

309
00:21:52,433 --> 00:21:54,000
- Your fault!
- Jobert!

310
00:21:54,133 --> 00:21:56,600
Your fault! Your fault!

311
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:07,300
Mom!

312
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:13,567
Jobert, I'm here!

313
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,500
Jobert, I'm here.

314
00:22:16,733 --> 00:22:17,933
Jobert...

315
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:19,467
I'm here.

316
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:22,333
Look at me. I'm here.

317
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:33,167
- It's okay.
- Sis, I'm sorry.

318
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:34,600
It's okay.

319
00:22:37,733 --> 00:22:40,667
It's okay.

320
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,167
I am here.

321
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,567
I am sorry, Marj.

322
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:47,600
I am sorry, Marj.

323
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:52,400
I am sorry, Marj.

324
00:22:55,400 --> 00:23:00,233
- It's okay. I'm here.
- I'm sorry, Sis.

325
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:01,567
I love you.

326
00:23:48,967 --> 00:23:50,467
I think he dreamed
about his mom.

327
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,567
That's probably why
he freaked out.

328
00:23:55,867 --> 00:23:56,800
You okay?

329
00:23:56,933 --> 00:23:58,567
He's okay now.

330
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:01,400
- Sorry again.
- Girl, it's fine.

331
00:24:08,133 --> 00:24:09,600
How's Jobert?

332
00:24:09,733 --> 00:24:11,333
He finally fell asleep.

333
00:24:11,467 --> 00:24:13,600
But he's still asking for Mom.

334
00:24:16,233 --> 00:24:18,300
Paolo, thank you.

335
00:24:18,433 --> 00:24:20,967
And sorry that
Jobert hurt you.

336
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:27,433
It's okay. I've had worse
beatings from girls I ghosted.

337
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:31,733
I feel bad for my brother.

338
00:24:31,867 --> 00:24:34,033
He misses our mom.

339
00:24:36,567 --> 00:24:37,867
If you don't mind me asking,

340
00:24:39,367 --> 00:24:41,133
why did your mom leave?

341
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:45,633
She went back to my
good-for-nothing dad.

342
00:24:47,533 --> 00:24:51,433
When my dad left,
life got really hard.

343
00:24:51,567 --> 00:24:54,900
I had no one to help me
take care of my brother.

344
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:56,800
It was all on me.

345
00:24:56,933 --> 00:25:00,500
I'm lucky Hannah's there.

346
00:25:00,633 --> 00:25:02,100
And you, too.

347
00:25:02,267 --> 00:25:04,433
But honestly,
it's really hard.

348
00:25:06,267 --> 00:25:08,100
I'm exhausted.

349
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:12,000
Doing everything alone is hard.

350
00:25:15,467 --> 00:25:16,400
Marj...

351
00:25:18,167 --> 00:25:19,867
you don't have to carry
everything by yourself.

352
00:25:21,733 --> 00:25:22,767
I'm here.

353
00:25:23,867 --> 00:25:27,033
Let me be here for you.

354
00:25:27,167 --> 00:25:29,667
Don't say that
if you're not serious.

355
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,033
Exactly, Marj.

356
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:45,333
I'm saying it
because I am serious.

357
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:50,033
I'm tired of being carefree.

358
00:25:50,167 --> 00:25:53,067
I'm tired of being a player.
I want something real.

359
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:56,300
I don't just want you
to be my girlfriend.

360
00:25:56,433 --> 00:25:58,333
I'm already thinking
about our future.

361
00:26:00,667 --> 00:26:01,667
Marj...

362
00:26:03,067 --> 00:26:04,933
I'm ready to get married.

363
00:26:11,967 --> 00:26:14,333
Looks like Sir Paolo's
living a new life, huh?

364
00:26:14,467 --> 00:26:16,767
That's the first time he's ever
brought a woman to the mansion.

365
00:26:16,900 --> 00:26:19,000
Why are you always so worried
about Edward?

366
00:26:19,133 --> 00:26:20,367
He's not like you.

367
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:21,867
Everyone loves you.

368
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:25,833
And now you've even taken
the girl he likes.

369
00:26:27,233 --> 00:26:29,433
You know what, I can't blame you
for not liking me.

370
00:26:29,567 --> 00:26:31,267
Even my own
father doesn't.

371
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:33,500
If you're jealous of your
brother because of Marj,

372
00:26:33,633 --> 00:26:35,467
don't drag the business
into it!

373
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:38,700
I can't shake this feeling
that something bad is coming.

374
00:26:40,433 --> 00:26:41,733
Marj...

375
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:43,600
it's nice to see you again.

376
00:26:43,733 --> 00:26:47,900
Even if you marry Paolo,
I will never accept you.

377
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:49,733
I'm the one playing this game.

378
00:26:49,867 --> 00:26:51,067
And I'm the one who will win.

379
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:55,067
Get ready to be miserable
in my house.

380
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,200
Welcome home, Marj.
